cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.NI

This paper discusses the profitability and cost of web-based cryptomining as a source of monetization for websites. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves the analysis of the impact of cryptomining on user experience and device performance. It may also fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it involves the measurement of network traffic and resource utilization. Finally, it may belong to the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the impact of web mining on network traffic.
